    • createSymbol

      public final TypeSymbol createSymbol(UMLGraphLayout layout, int details, boolean isFocusClass)
      Creates the SVG symbol that represents this type element for the UML diagram.
      Parameters:
      layout - The instance of UMLGraphLayout that is used to render the document that finally contains the SVGSymbol instance that is created by this method.
      details - The level of detail to show:
      • 0: no details, only class name and package name; for an enum also the enum constants
      • 1: only elements should be shown that are relevant for the API
      • 2: all elements should be shown.
      isFocusClass - true if this class is the focus class of the graph.
      Returns:
      The SVG symbol instance that represents the UML diagram for this class.

    • determineStereotypes

      final String[] determineStereotypes()
      Determines the stereotypes for this UML class doc. It will be inferred from the type of the class. The stereotype «Interface» is used for an interface, «Enum» for an enum type, and «Annotation» for an annotation.

      A regular class that is derived from Error will have the stereotype «Error», or «Exception» if derived from Exception.

      An abstract class will have the stereotype «Type», a class with only static methods (or no methods at all) the stereotype «Utility».

      If none of the conditions above will fit, we have a simple class without a particular stereotype.
      Returns:
      The list of stereotypes defined for this UML type element; it may be empty, but will never be null.
